Package uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.owl.triples

Provides abstract extension of ORMatcher for matcher implementations based on specific types of RDF triples store.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    OTFactory
    Interface representing implementation-specific data-factories
    OTGraphAdder
    Represents a named graph being added to the triple store.
    OTGraphRemover
    Represents a named graph being removed from the triple store.
    OTQuery
    Represents a particular SPARQL query.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    OT_URI
    Represents a URI used in a triple.
    OTMatcher
    Extension of ORMatcher that represents the instances via sets of triples in an RDF triple store, and the queries as SPARQL queries over that store.
    OTNumber
    Represents a number used as an object in a triple.
    OTQueryConstants
    Represents the constants for a particular SPARQL query, mapping each constant to a variable-name that appears in the initial version of the query-string, with implementation classes being responsible for performing the necessary pre-execution substitution operations.
    OTString
    Represents a string used as an object in a triple.
    OTValue
    Represents a value used in a triple, either a URI, a number, or a string.
    OTValueVisitor
    Visitor for OTValue-derived objects.
